cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about synthesizing high-resolution photographic images using a novel introspective variational autoencoder (IntroVAE) model. The paper focuses on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (LG) techniques for image synthesis, which suggests that cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models (AI) and neural networks (NE) for training the IntroVAE model. Finally, the paper presents experimental results on generating photo-realistic images, which suggests that cs.MM (multimedia) could also be a relevant sub-category.
